        [
            {
                "type": "text",
                "textType": "title",
                "html": "MONTHLY BUDGET"
            },
            {
                "type": "grid",
                "columnWeights": [0.7, 0.3],
                "spacing": 20,
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "element": {
                            "type": "quoteblock",
                            "html": "Calculating monthly budgets helps keep finances in order throughout the year and it ensures that there are enough financial resources even in the later months of the school year. "
                        },
                        "position": [1, 1],
                        "size": [1, 1]
                    },
                    {
                        "element": {
                            "type": "titledblock",
                            "title": "instructions",
                            "html": "Take a look at the monthly totals in the annual expense sheet. These totals give a general idea of how much funding is needed per month. However, some expenses, like tuition, come in one lump sum instead of an even bill per month. Collect information for your anticipated expenses, and fill in each category accordingly. The pie and bar charts help visualize and compare your running totals per month. If there are unexpected expenses or higher expenditure than planned, reassess as needed, the charts are interactive!"
                        },
                        "position": [1, 2],
                        "size": [1, 1]
                    },
                    {
                        "element": {
                            "type": "titledblock",
                            "title": "helpful hints",
                            "html": "<ul><li>Planning to put aside money for unexpected expenses is a stress reducing habit. When emergencies or unplanned situations occur, you would already have a buffer fund prepared.</li><li>Similar to the unexpected expenses fund, a savings fund helps prepare you for your future goals, and builds a safety net for unanticipated circumstances.</li><li>Post secondary education is a notoriously expensive time in life so organizing finances varies a lot from situation to situation. Generally, allocating 30% of your monthly financial resources towards rent and utitilites is typical. Another 30% towards other essential life expenses is also common practice.</li><li>Some people find it helpful to add fee due dates to their phone calendar so that they receive notification in advance, and avoid late payment fees.</li><li>For folks who struggle keeping to budgets, setting limits on cards or withdrawing a finite amount of cash for the month can help reinforce financial goals.</li></ul>"
                        },
                        "position": [1, 3],
                        "size": [2, 1]
                    },
                    {
                        "element": {
                            "type": "verticallist",
                            "title": "To Do:",
                            "elements": [
                                {
                                    "type": "checkbox",
                                    "checkbox": "true",
                                    "label": "TAKE A LOOK AT THE MONTHLY TOTALS IN THE ANNUAL EXPENSE SHEET"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "checkbox",
                                    "checkbox": "true",
                                    "label": "COLLECT ITEMIZED EXPENSES INFO"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "checkbox",
                                    "checkbox": "true",
                                    "label": "Compare the totals"
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "checkbox",
                                    "checkbox": "true",
                                    "label": "REASSESS AS NEEDED"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        "position": [2, 1],
                        "size": [1, 2]
                    }
                ]
            }
